**business case**

- developing the business case

1 define the measureable organizational value 
	
2 form a cross function business case team
	advantages
		> credibility
		> alignment of goals
		> access to real costs 
		> etc 
3 identifying alternatives
	possible options
		> change existing process without investing IT
		> dont do it
4 feasability and assess risk
	feasibility : worth doing? 
		> economic
		> technical
		> organizational
		> other
	risk
		> identification
		> assessment
		> response
5 define total cost of ownership
	direct or up front costs
	ongoing costs
	indirect costs
6 defien total benefits of ownership
	increase high value work
	imporving accuracy and efficiency
	improving decision making
	improving cusomer service

- breakeven

	even profit
